eeted.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the myth\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1383}, {\"ngram\": \"the officials\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You heard it first from @TeamIreland gymnast @McClenaghanRhys - the sustainable cardboard beds are sturdy!\\\"\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"@TeamIreland\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnast @McClenaghanRhys\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"the sustainable cardboard beds\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, many have a different perception of COVID's contagiousness, leading some athletes to question the resurgence of the cardboard beds for the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a different perception\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"COVID's contagiousness\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"some athletes\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"the resurgence\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"the cardboard beds\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic officials clarified in a recentTikTokwhy the beds are still useful: they are sustainable.\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic officials\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"a recentTikTokwhy\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"the beds\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1736}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While they are the same style as used for the Tokyo Olympics, they are \\\"100% made in France\\\" and consist of three \\\"modules\\\" meant to allow athletes to adjust the firmness and length based on their size.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1862, \"end\": 1868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\",